<item>
            <title>[IMAGING-279] Array sizes not checked for overflow in BmpImageParser</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IMAGING-279</link>
                <project id="12313421" key="IMAGING">Commons Imaging</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In BmpImageParser.readImageContents, it is not verified that &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=commons-imaging.git;a=blob;f=src/main/java/org/apache/commons/imaging/formats/bmp/BmpImageParser.java;h=09d560011ebbde5ea8df65a30ea9692c2e697d17;hb=HEAD#l441&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;imageDataSize&lt;/a&gt; does not overflow. If it does, BinaryFunctions.readBytes crashes with an uncaught NegativeArraySizeException.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13352230">IMAGING-279</key>
